International Children's Day Celebrated in Lhasa 
More than 5,000 children in this capital of the Tibet Autonomous Region
today gathered at the Potala Palace to celebrate International
Children's Day.
The children, from 24 middle and primary schools here, put on a group
performance.
Prior to the performance, the children attended a solemn ceremony to
watch the raising of the national flag and sing the national anthem.
Many of the children expressed their joy in their lives.
